BT /F2 21 Tf 58 701.00 Td (Smart City Transportation Network) Tj ET
BT /F2 21 Tf 58 681.50 Td (Optimization) Tj ET
BT /F2 15 Tf 58 654.00 Td (Code-Focused Technical Report) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 624.50 Td (Stack: Python, Streamlit, Plotly Mapbox, pandas, scikit-learn, Docker) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 58 600.00 Td (1. Technical Overview) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 579.50 Td (This project is a Python smart-city transportation system that combines algorithms with an) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 566.00 Td (interactive Streamlit dashboard. Cairo is modeled as a weighted graph where nodes are) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 552.50 Td (locations and edges are roads. The system applies graph algorithms, dynamic programming,) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 539.00 Td (greedy optimization, and machine learning to transportation planning problems.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 520.50 Td (The application is integrated rather than a collection of separate scripts. The graph is) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 507.00 Td (loaded once, shared across modules, visualized through reusable Plotly map logic, and exposed) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 493.50 Td (through a multi-page Streamlit UI.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.4 Tf 58 475.00 Td (- UI layer: app.py handles navigation, KPI cards, tabs, maps, and user controls.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.4 Tf 58 460.50 Td (- Graph layer: data_loader1.py loads nodes.csv and edges.csv into CairoGraph.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.4 Tf 58 446.00 Td (- Algorithm layer: dijkstra.py, astar.py, kruskal_mst.py, dp_maintenance.py,) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.4 Tf 58 432.50 Td (  public_transit_scheduler.py, and greedy.py.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.4 Tf 58 418.00 Td (- Prediction layer: traffic_ml_model.py trains and serves Random Forest traffic predictions.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.4 Tf 58 403.50 Td (- Deployment layer: Dockerfile, requirements.txt, and .dockerignore package the project.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 58 383.00 Td (2. Code Architecture) Tj ET
BT /F2 11.2 Tf 58 360.50 Td (2.1 Graph Model) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 343.00 Td (CairoGraph stores nodes, edges, and adjacency_list. nodes is a dictionary indexed by node ID,) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 329.50 Td (edges is a list of Edge objects, and adjacency_list maps each node to outgoing road edges.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.6 Tf 72 311.00 Td (graph.nodes          # { node_id: Node }) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.6 Tf 72 297.50 Td (graph.edges          # all Edge objects) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.6 Tf 72 284.00 Td (graph.adjacency_list # { node_id: [Edge, ...] }) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 265.50 Td (The graph loader creates reverse edges for undirected road traversal. Without reverse) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 252.00 Td (adjacency entries, Dijkstra or A* could fail to find routes that should exist in the physical) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 238.50 Td (road network.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11.2 Tf 58 218.00 Td (2.2 Streamlit State And Caching) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 200.50 Td (The app uses st.session_state for route results, active page, chaos simulation edges, selected) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 187.00 Td (time of day, and UI choices. The graph is loaded with st.cache_resource so it is not rebuilt) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 173.50 Td (on every widget interaction.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.6 Tf 72 155.00 Td (@st.cache_resource\(show_spinner=False\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.6 Tf 72 141.50 Td (def load_graph\(\):) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.6 Tf 72 128.00 Td (    graph = CairoGraph\(\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.6 Tf 72 114.50 Td (    graph.load_data\(nodes_path, edges_path\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.6 Tf 72 101.00 Td (    return graph) Tj ET
BT /F1 8 Tf 58 30 Td (Smart City Transportation Network Optimization - Code-Focused Technical Report - Page 1) Tj ET
