BT /F2 14 Tf 58 729.00 Td (3. Algorithm Implementation Details) Tj ET
BT /F2 11.2 Tf 58 706.50 Td (3.1 Dijkstra Routing) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 689.00 Td (Dijkstra finds the shortest or fastest path between two nodes using non-negative edge weights.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 675.50 Td (The weight can come from static distance or from graph.get_weight\(\) when the traffic predictor) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 662.00 Td (is active. With a priority queue, complexity is O\(\(V + E\) log V\).) Tj ET
BT /F2 11.2 Tf 58 641.50 Td (3.2 A* Emergency Routing) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 624.00 Td (A* uses f\(n\) = g\(n\) + h\(n\), where h\(n\) is a geographic distance heuristic. This helps) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 610.50 Td (emergency routing because the search is guided toward the hospital and usually explores fewer) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 597.00 Td (nodes than Dijkstra.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11.2 Tf 58 576.50 Td (3.3 Kruskal MST Road Expansion) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 559.00 Td (Kruskal's algorithm uses Union-Find with path compression and union by rank. Existing roads) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 545.50 Td (are connected first, then potential roads are sorted by construction cost. The dominant cost) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 532.00 Td (is sorting, so complexity is O\(E log E\).) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.6 Tf 72 513.50 Td (if uf.union\(edge.from_id, edge.to_id\):) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.6 Tf 72 500.00 Td (    chosen_roads.append\(edge\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.6 Tf 72 486.50 Td (    total_cost += actual_cost) Tj ET
BT /F2 11.2 Tf 58 466.00 Td (3.4 Maintenance DP Knapsack) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 448.50 Td (Road maintenance is a 0/1 Knapsack problem. Each candidate road has repair_cost and) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 435.00 Td (repair_value. The DP table has dimensions \(n + 1\) by \(budget + 1\). Backtracking through the) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 421.50 Td (table returns the exact roads selected for repair.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.6 Tf 72 403.00 Td (dp[i][w] = dp[i - 1][w]) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.6 Tf 72 389.50 Td (if w >= cost:) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.6 Tf 72 376.00 Td (    dp[i][w] = max\(dp[i][w], dp[i - 1][w - cost] + value\)) Tj ET
BT /F2 11.2 Tf 58 355.50 Td (3.5 Bus Allocation DP) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 338.00 Td (The bus scheduler uses dynamic programming to distribute a limited fleet across routes. This) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 324.50 Td (avoids the weakness of a greedy approach that might assign too many buses to the single) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 311.00 Td (highest-demand route.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11.2 Tf 58 290.50 Td (3.6 Greedy Signal Control) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 273.00 Td (The signal controller uses a greedy decision rule for fast local optimization. It is useful) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 259.50 Td (for real-time simulation, but it can be suboptimal if downstream congestion is ignored.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 58 235.00 Td (4. Code-Level Problems Faced And Fixes) Tj ET
BT /F2 11.2 Tf 58 212.50 Td (4.1 Maintenance DP Used A Different Visualization Path) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 195.00 Td (The Maintenance DP algorithm produced correct values, but its visualization did not match the) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 181.50 Td (rest of the app. It was displayed separately from the shared Plotly Mapbox renderer, causing) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 168.00 Td (inconsistent styling and interaction.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 149.50 Td (Fix: build_map\(\) in app.py was extended with a maintenance_result parameter so maintenance can) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 136.00 Td (reuse the same Cairo basemap, node rendering, layout, and Streamlit map behavior.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.6 Tf 72 117.50 Td (def build_map\(..., maintenance_result=None\):) Tj ET
BT /F1 8.6 Tf 72 104.00 Td (    maintenance_mode = maintenance_result is not None) Tj ET
BT /F1 8 Tf 58 30 Td (Smart City Transportation Network Optimization - Code-Focused Technical Report - Page 2) Tj ET
endstream
