BT /F2 14 Tf 58 729.00 Td (8. Complexity Summary) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.4 Tf 58 708.50 Td (- Dijkstra: O\(\(V + E\) log V\) with a priority queue.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.4 Tf 58 694.00 Td (- A*: usually explores fewer nodes when the heuristic is informative.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.4 Tf 58 679.50 Td (- Kruskal MST: O\(E log E\), dominated by sorting.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.4 Tf 58 665.00 Td (- Maintenance DP: O\(nW\), where n is roads and W is budget.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.4 Tf 58 650.50 Td (- Bus allocation DP: depends on route count and fleet size.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.4 Tf 58 636.00 Td (- Greedy signal control: fast local choice, approximately O\(k\) for k incoming roads.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 58 615.50 Td (9. Conclusion) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 595.00 Td (The project successfully combines multiple algorithmic techniques into one smart-city) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 581.50 Td (transportation dashboard. The biggest recent improvement was fixing the Maintenance DP) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 568.00 Td (visualization and making map interaction consistent across the application.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 549.50 Td (The challenges were mostly integration issues: connecting algorithm results to shared) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 536.00 Td (visualization, preserving Streamlit state, separating existing roads from candidate roads,) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 522.50 Td (handling Docker runtime dependencies, and supporting deployment ports. Solving these issues) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.6 Tf 58 509.00 Td (made the system more professional, reliable, and easier to use.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8 Tf 58 30 Td (Smart City Transportation Network Optimization - Code-Focused Technical Report - Page 5) Tj ET
endstream
